ex.d.ts","_npmUser":{"name":"nodejs-team","email":"nodejs-team@bytedance.com"},"dist":{"integrity":"sha512-cXTaNMW067k4veC/QVZ9Pz6WJwHhuatkY/TNic8o1/g7kx5acwr90EH4zDuT+LJDZjnVOl5FxgN8s//gnuXUSQ==","shasum":"156bafb5ea0d3ad5d6948a5626f8b7eef11e3300","size":7139,"tarball":"https://bnpm.byted.org/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul/-/fetch-protocol-consul-2.3.1-beta.0.tgz","unpackedSize":25491,"fileCount":12},"engines":{"node":">=10.0.0"},"files":["lib"],"name":"@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul","_id":"@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul@2.3.1-beta.0","_nodeVersion":"14.20.0","author":"","description":"consul protocol for @byted-service/fetch","version":"2.3.1-beta.0","_npmVersion":"lerna/undefined/node@v14.20.0+x64 (linux)","dependencies":{"@byted-service/consul":"^2.1.5","@byted-service/fetch-core":"^2.4.2","@byted-service/logger":"^2.1.2","@byted/node-fetch":"^2.6.5","tslib":"^1.9.3"},"license":"MIT","main":"lib/index.js","maintainers":[{"avatar":"https://s3-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/bf5207f4-07f4-4c43-9004-b01af1aff365~?image_size=72x72&cut_type=&quality=&format=png&sticker_format=.webp","email":"liyubei@bytedance.com","name":"liyubei"},{"avatar":"","email":"nodejs-team@bnpm.com","name":"nodejs-team"},{"avatar":"https://s1-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/d27d000e276d58ace3df~?image_size=72x72&cut_type=&quality=&format=png&sticker_format=.webp","email":"ouyangyadong@bytedance.com","name":"ouyangyadong"},{"avatar":"https://s1-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/a339a912-f731-4fe7-9e51-d91e1871180g~?image_size=240x240&cut_type=&quality=&format=image&sticker_format=.webp","email":"xieda@bytedance.com","name":"xieda"}],"gitHead":"13075453c4c5fb6285e099d1fe0e6337da5d831d","readme":"# @byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul\n\n[![bnpm](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/badge/v/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul.svg?style=flat-square)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul) [![download](https://2y8ngapf.fn.bytedance.net/d?p=@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul)\n\n[简体中文](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/fetch-protocol-consul/README.md) | [English](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/fetch-protocol-consul/README.en.md) | [CHANGELOG](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/fetch-protocol-consul/CHANGELOG.md)\n\n> The following is **@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul@2.x** document, **1.x** document see [fetch-v1.x](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/tree/fetch-v1.x/packages/fetch-protocol-consul), [@byted-service/fetch@2.0.0 release log](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnMNUcH3YbXKEeZSX4YqCavc).\n\n`@byted-service/fetch` consul protocol extention.\n\n1. support `consul://p.s.m/xxx`, [Node.js Service Discovery (Consul) User Guide](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnU8nNhyPfhV2OjHLCVQPX5g), [A Quick Start with Service Discovery ( Consul ) for Front-End Engineers](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcn9QfY7pMwo9I9Jf1Y2q6R4d).\n2. suport [ByteMesh](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcn3Kazqb9H1MZsHBet1q6RGc), [ByteMesh HTTP/1.1 & HTTP/2 protocol access agreement](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnBvELWkcTSb7PMU3H0GoRqd).\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install @byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul --registry=http://bnpm.byted.org\n```\n\n## Quick Start\n\n> Currently it is built-in in @byted-service/fetch, actually can be used without any operation.\n\n```ts\nimport { fetch } from '@byted-service/fetch';\nimport { protocol, handle } from '@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul';\n\nfetch.register(protocol, handle);\n\n(async () => {\n    const resp = await fetch('consul://p.s.m/xxx');\n\n    console.log(await resp.text());\n})();\n```\n\n## API\n\n### fetch(url[, options])\n\nThe parameters of `@byted-service/fetch` have been extended. Generally, It is set by framework , and user unaware.\n\n<details>\n  <summary>History</summary>\n\n-   `v2.1.0`\n    -   Mark `options.consulClient`, `options.consulClientOptions`, `options.disableMesh` as deprecated.\n    -   Support `options.consulOption`, `options.consulLookupOption`, `options.enableMesh`.\n\n</details>\n\n-   `url`: request url.\n-   `options`:\n    -   `consul`: `Consul` instance, see [@byted-service/consul](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/consul/README.en.md).\n    -   `consulOptions`: `Consul` construction options, see [@byted-service/consul](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/consul/README.en.md).\n    -   `consulLookupOptions`: `consul.lookup()` options, see [@byted-service/consul](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/consul/README.en.md).\n    -   `enableMesh`: Whether to send request through `http egress mesh`, the default value is `true`.\n\n## Mesh\n\nStarting from `@byted-service/fetch@1.6.0`, when the `tce` cluster is configured according to https://bytedance.feishu.cn/space/doc/doccnjPUcpCENG6vktQYID, requests in the form of `consul:` will be sent through the mesh proxy.\n\nIf it is in `faas && enable mesh and SERVICE_MESH_HTTP_EGRESS_ADDR is existed`, consul protocol will use [@byted/node-fetch](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-node-fetch) to initiate a request.\n\n## Metrics\n\nRelated indicators and tags are the same as [@byted-service/fetch](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/fetch/README.en.md#metrics), the modified part is listed below.\n\n-   `to`: Server psm.\n-   `to_cluster`: Server cluster, can be set by `options.consul.cluster`, the result of consul service discovery may be changed after modification.\n-   `to_idc`: Server idc, can be set by `options.consul.idc`, the result of consul service discovery may be changed after modification.\n-   `mesh`: Whether use http egress mesh, the default is `0`, judge according to environment variables and `options.disableMesh`.\n    -   `0`: No, `options.disableMesh = false` or `process.env.TCE_ENABLE_HTTP_SIDECAR_EGRESS !=='True'`, at this time, the address after consul service discovery will be requested.\n    -   `1`: Yes, `options.disableMesh = true` or `process.env.TCE_ENABLE_HTTP_SIDECAR_EGRESS ==='True'`, at this time, if on faas, `process.env.SERVICE_MESH_HTTP_EGRESS_ADDR` will be requested, otherwise, `127.0.0.1:process. env.MESH_EGRESS_PORT`.\n-   `ipv6`: The consul service found whether the returned ipv6 address, the default is `0`.\n    -   `0`: No.\n    -   `1`: Yes.\n\n## Logger\n\nRelated tags are the same as [@byted-service/fetch](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/fetch/README.en.md#logger), the modified part is listed below.\n\n<details>\n  <summary>History</summary>\n\n-   `v2.1.0`: Remove `is_fass_http_egress`.\n\n</details>\n\n-   `to`: Server psm.\n-   `to_cluster`: Server cluster, can be set by `options.consul.cluster`, the result of consul service discovery may be changed after modification.\n-   `to_idc`: Server idc, can be set by `options.consul.idc`, the result of consul service discovery may be changed after modification.\n-   `mesh`: Whether use http egress mesh, the default is `0`, judge according to environment variables and `options.disableMesh`.\n    -   `0`: No, `options.disableMesh = false` or `process.env.TCE_ENABLE_HTTP_SIDECAR_EGRESS !=='True'`, at this time, the address after consul service discovery will be requested.\n    -   `1`: Yes, `options.disableMesh = true` or `process.env.TCE_ENABLE_HTTP_SIDECAR_EGRESS ==='True'`, at this time, if on faas, `process.env.SERVICE_MESH_HTTP_EGRESS_ADDR` will be requested, otherwise, `127.0.0.1:process. env.MESH_EGRESS_PORT`.\n-   `rip`: Real request ip.\n-   `ipv6`: The consul service found whether the returned ipv6 address, the default is `0`.\n    -   `0`: No.\n    -   `1`: Yes.\n","readmeFilename":"README.en.md","repository":{"type":"git","url":"https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service"}},"1.0.1":{"_npmVersion":"6.14.5","readmeFilename":"README.md","types":"lib/index.d.ts","version":"1.0.1","_id":"@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul@1.0.1","_nodeVersion":"14.5.0","devDependencies":{"@types/lodash.pick":"^4.4.6","lodash.pick":"^4.4.0"},"maintainers":[{"avatar":"https://s3-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/bf5207f4-07f4-4c43-9004-b01af1aff365~?image_size=72x72&cut_type=&quality=&format=png&sticker_format=.webp","email":"liyubei@bytedance.com","name":"liyubei"},{"avatar":"","email":"nodejs-team@bnpm.com","name":"nodejs-team"},{"avatar":"https://s1-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/d27d000e276d58ace3df~?image_size=72x72&cut_type=&quality=&format=png&sticker_format=.webp","email":"ouyangyadong@bytedance.com","name":"ouyangyadong"},{"avatar":"https://s1-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/a339a912-f731-4fe7-9e51-d91e1871180g~?image_size=240x240&cut_type=&quality=&format=image&sticker_format=.webp","email":"xieda@bytedance.com","name":"xieda"}],"scripts":{"prepublish":"npm run build","test":"RUNTIME_IDC_NAME=lf ../../node_modules/.bin/jest --config ./jest.config.json --coverage --env=node","build":"rm -rf lib && ../../node_modules/.bin/tsc"},"_npmUser":{"name":"xieda","email":"xieda@bytedance.com"},"dependencies":{"tslib":"^1.9.3","@byted-service/consul":"^1.9.0","@byted-service/env":"^1.7.0","@byted-service/fetch-core":"^1.0.0","@byted-service/helper":"^1.4.0","@byted-service/mesh":">=1.3.0","@byted/node-fetch":"^2.6.3"},"dist":{"size":5255,"tarball":"https://bnpm.byted.org/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul/-/fetch-protocol-consul-1.0.1.tgz","key":"/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul/-/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul-1.0.1.tgz","shasum":"019f5a30f056355e4ad3fb13023590c1713fb839"},"license":"ISC","name":"@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul","repository":{"type":"git","url":"https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/packages/fetch-protocol-consul"},"publish_time":1603356441619,"_cnpm_publish_time":1603356441619,"_publish_on_cnpm":true,"description":"consul protocol for @byted-serivce/fetch","files":["lib"],"keywords":["fetch","consul"],"main":"lib/index.js"},"1.2.6-alpha.0":{"devDependencies":{"@types/lodash.pick":"^4.4.6","lodash.pick":"^4.4.0"},"files":["lib"],"gitHead":"5ae5459e7f9de4e702095f7bc9af381ccb685510","readme":"# @byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul\n\n`@byted-service/fetch` consul protocol extention\n\n1. support `consul://p.s.m/xxx`, [Service Discovery (Consul) quick start for Front End](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnK9K2hSJlEWhOdZxwzmXOxb#)\n2. suport [ByteMesh](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcn3Kazqb9H1MZsHBet1q6RGc)，[ByteMesh HTTP/1.1 & HTTP/2 protocol access agreement](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnBvELWkcTSb7PMU3H0GoRqd)\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install @byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul --registry=http://bnpm.byted.org\n```\n\n## quick start\n\n> Currently it is built-in in @byted-service/fetch, actually can be used without any operation\n\n```ts\nimport fetch from '@byted-service/fetch';\nimport { protocol, handle } from '@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul';\n\nfetch.register(protocol, handle);\n\n(async () => {\n    const resp = await fetch('consul://p.s.m/xxx');\n\n    console.log(await resp.text());\n})();\n```\n\n## API\n\n### fetch(url[, options])\n\nThe parameters of @byted-service/fetch have been extended. Generally, It is set by framework , and user unaware.\n\n-   `url`: request url\n-   `options`:\n    -   `consulClient`: `@byted-service/consul` instance, no need to pay attention in most cases\n    -   `consulClientOptions`: `@byted-service/consul` config options, no need to pay attention in most cases\n    -   `consul`: The calling parameters of `consul.random` can be filtered by setting `env` and `cluster` to filter the ip:port combinations that need to be filtered, no need to pay attention in most cases\n\n## Mesh\n\nStarting from `@byted-service/fetch@1.6.0`, when the tce cluster is configured according to https://bytedance.feishu.cn/space/doc/doccnjPUcpCENG6vktQYID, requests in the form of `consul:` will be sent through the mesh proxy\n\nIf it is in faas && enable mesh and SERVICE_MESH_HTTP_EGRESS_ADDR is existed, consul protocol will use [@byted/node-fetch](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-node-fetch) to initiate a request.\n\n## Metrics\n\nRelated indicators and tags are the same as [@byted-service/fetch](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/fetch/README.en.md#metrics), the modified part is listed below\n\n-   to: Server psm\n-   to_cluster: Server cluster, can be set by `options.consul.cluster`, the result of consul service discovery may be changed after modification\n-   to_idc: Server idc, can be set by `options.consul.idc`, the result of consul service discovery may be changed after modification\n-   mesh: Whether use http egress mesh, the default is `0`, judge according to environment variables and `options.disableMesh`\n    -   0: No, `options.disableMesh = false` or `process.env.TCE_ENABLE_HTTP_SIDECAR_EGRESS !=='True'`, at this time, the address after consul service discovery will be requested\n    -   1: Yes, `options.disableMesh = true` or `process.env.TCE_ENABLE_HTTP_SIDECAR_EGRESS ==='True'`, at this time, if on faas, `process.env.SERVICE_MESH_HTTP_EGRESS_ADDR` will be requested, otherwise, `127.0.0.1:process. env.MESH_EGRESS_PORT`\n-   ipv6: The consul service found whether the returned ipv6 address, the default is `0`\n    -   0: No\n    -   1: Yes\n\n## Logger\n\nRelated tags are the same as [@byted-service/fetch](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/fetch/README.en.md#logger), the modified part is listed below\n\n-   to: Server psm\n-   to_cluster: Server cluster, can be set by `options.consul.cluster`, the result of consul service discovery may be changed after modification\n-   to_idc: Server idc, can be set by `options.consul.idc`, the result of consul service discovery may be changed after modification\n-   mesh: Whether use http egress mesh, the default is `0`, judge according to environment variables and `options.disableMesh`\n    -   0: No, `options.disableMesh = false` or `process.env.TCE_ENABLE_HTTP_SIDECAR_EGRESS !=='True'`, at this time, the address after consul service discovery will be requested\n    -   1: Yes, `options.disableMesh = true` or `process.env.TCE_ENABLE_HTTP_SIDECAR_EGRESS ==='True'`, at this time, if on faas, `process.env.SERVICE_MESH_HTTP_EGRESS_ADDR` will be requested, otherwise, `127.0.0.1:process. env.MESH_EGRESS_PORT`\n-   rip: Real request ip\n-   is_fass_http_egress: Is it faas http egress mesh\n-   ipv6: The consul service found whether the returned ipv6 address, the default is `0`\n    -   0: No\n    -   1: Yes\n","_id":"@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul@1.2.6-alpha.0","_npmUser":{"email":"shanshengkai@bytedance.com","name":"shanshengkai"},"_npmVersion":"8.19.2","description":"consul protocol for @byted-service/fetch","keywords":["fetch","consul"],"readmeFilename":"README.en.md","version":"1.2.6-alpha.0","dependencies":{"@byted-service/consul":"^2.1.5","@byted-service/fetch-core":"^1.4.3","@byted-service/helper":"^1.6.2","@byted-service/mesh":"^1.4.1","@byted/node-fetch":"^2.6.3","tslib":"^1.9.3"},"license":"ISC","_nodeVersion":"16.17.1","dist":{"shasum":"be166784c720a760d14f66782051dd7c2450fab6","size":6999,"tarball":"https://bnpm.byted.org/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-consul/-/fetch-protocol-consul-1.2.6-alpha.0.tgz","unpackedSize":23361,"fileCount":9,"integrity":"sha512-jDRJ3SwUlNfAJNr1CiWfYcAMtSP7VSNg2/Lb7/BbXL9xEonCVqkPFNR5dAyvJawdgp+TgvoDy/amoJA0MZQbnQ=="},"main":"lib/index.js","maintainers":[{"avatar":"https://s3-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/bf5207f4-07f4-4c43-9004-b01af1aff365~?image_size=72x72&cut_type=&quality=&format=png&sticker_format=.webp","email":"liyubei@bytedance.com","name":"liyubei"},{"email":"nodejs-team@bnpm.com","name":"nodejs-team","avatar":""},{"avatar":"https://s1-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/d27d000e276d58ace3df~?image_s